narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you need a B.S. in Biology, you have to take it!
pick something you enjoy because it will take up a lot of your time. but if you do, you'll love it.

You get to do independent research with a faculty mentor- its a really great way to learn about the research process. I used Peabody museum collections, which I highly recommend- the curators and collections managers are AMAZING, have hundreds of awesome research ideas, and let you design your own project and really take the reins. (Particularly, vertebrate and invertebrate zoology and vertebrate and invertebrate paleontology -- these happen to be the fields I have studied.) Chris Norris and Leo Buss were the people I worked with, and they are really brilliant and helpful with the research process. Analysis is based solely on your final paper, which isn't a big problem since you work on it for the whole semester.
